The paper deals with automatic tumor segmentation in breast ultrasound images, which is a problem in computer vision (CV). The proposed approach involves modeling radiologists' attention mechanism, which is a common technique in artificial intelligence (AI) research. The paper also mentions using a weighted map, which is a common technique in machine learning (ML) and deep learning (DL) research. Therefore, cs.CV and cs.AI are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also involves experimentation and evaluation of the proposed approach, which falls under the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), multimedia (cs.MM), and information retrieval (cs.IR).
